  "text": "Other work suggests that these new media might be treated in fundamentally different ways from their physical counterparts. In a recent study of sound memorabilia, we found that recording practices were very different from more traditional types of mementos [CITATION_1] . Participants were not content to use sound to passively record events, instead they constructed and manipulated the situation to represent key events in a special way, e.g. to record 'radio plays' or interviews about key holiday events. It may be that developing new tools for capture and playback of conversational or sound mementos will lead to very different experiences and practices than those used for more visual or object-centric memorabilia.",
